<HEADLINE>
COMING: PARADE OF NEW MODELS 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (l and f coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JERRY MORRIS  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The new cars continue to roll out of the factories.
</P>
<P>
   Coming soon are a new Neon, a new sporty Honda Civic, an S model
from Jaguar, new Chevrolets, Buicks, Pontiacs, a small Lincoln, and
vans and trucks. While most of these will be out this spring, they
will be racing to be the first of the 2000 models, not 1999s.
</P>
<P>
   The '99 model year brings with it not only new models, but also
new car companies and new quality standards. Mercedes-Benz, which
has been setting the standards for technology and quality for
years, will raise that benchmark with its all new S-Class flagship
sedan. Consider just a few of the features of the new V8-powered
sedan: It will be leaner by 500 pounds than previous models, giving
it more fuel efficiency; it will be three inches shorter, yet add
an inch of space to the already spacious rear-seat area.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, the car's airbags will automatically adjust for
low- or high-speed collisions; it will have side airbags on all
four doors, as well as front airbags and head-protection curtain
airbags; a satellite-based navigation system will be standard; and
the climate control will be ``smart,'' adjusting for both where the
sun is shining and where the passenger is sitting. Controls on the
steering wheel will direct many of the car's systems and also
diagnose any faults that occur. The S-Class will also have a smart
cruise-control system that will automatically maintain a pre-set
distance behind the car in front.
</P>
<P>
   The new Dodge/Plymouth Neon is entering the marketplace and the
2000 model year Neon will sport a quieter 132-horsepower engine.
Chrysler says the new car is longer, wider, more solid and sports a
more controlled ride.
</P>
<P>
   The Civic Si brings youthful excitement to the Honda line.
Honda, recognizing that many drivers like to lower and customize
Civics, has designed the Si to appeal to that market. For
performance, the Si has a 1.6-liter dual overhead cam VTEC
four-cylinder engine that boasts 160 horsepower, tops of any
vehicle in the compact class, Honda says. Priced at around $17,000,
the Si comes with customized exhaust system, special suspension and
slightly different looks. For liability reasons, Honda has chosen
not to lower the vehicle.
</P>
<P>
   This spring, Jaguar will introduce a sedan in the $40,000 range.
The S-type model will have a choice of specially tuned V6 and V8
engines. Also featured will be a navigation system and
voice-activated controls. The new Jaguar will be a companion to the
Lincoln LS-series. The new rear-drive Lincoln also will have a
choice of V6 and V8 engines along with a five-speed automatic. The
V6 will be offered with a five-speed manual. Take that as a sign
the times they are a-changing.
</P>
<P>
   Other models to look for will be a new Buick LeSabre and Pontiac
Bonneville, offering new ride comfort and handling. Chevrolet
brings back the Impala, a full-sized front-drive car with V6 power.
</P>
<P>
   From Europe will come a replacement for the Ford Escort. Saab
will introduce its 9-5 wagon, loaded with safety features, space
and a choice of a turbocharged four-cylinder or V6 engine. Nissan
is introducing a newly redesigned Maxima and Mazda will offer a new
MPV minivan with dual sliding doors, larger interior and a carlike
ride.
</P>
<P>
   Toyota is going all out with its new Tundra truck. The Tundra,
built in America, is designed to take on Ford's top selling F
series. It will be loaded with features, choices of wheelbases and
engines. Four-wheel drive will also be offered.
</P>
<P>
   Spicing up the truck field, Ford is planning on a little bit of
thunder of its own with the F-150 SVT Lightening. The Lightening
will boast a 325 horsepower V8 and ride on 18-inch performance
tires.
</P>
<P>
   Not only is the Hyundai Sonata a totally new car, but it also
boasts one of the best warranties of any car at any price. The
Sonata has not only a new body, but also two new engines, three new
transmissions, a new double-wishbone suspension, and added safety
features including side airbags. The family-sized Sonata sedan
comes with a five-year, 60,000-mile bumper-to-bumper warranty and a
10-year powertrain guarantee. Add to this a 24-hour roadside
assistance plan good for five years. With its pricing, warranty
protection and new quality standards, Hyundai deserves a fresh
look.
</P>
<P>
   New on the scene from Korea is Daewoo, a company with unusual
marketing ideas. For now, the only showroom for Daewoo is in Natick
because the company is depending on college students to market the
cars by word of mouth. Daewoo recently announced it would sell
cars, at least in California, over the Internet. Daewoos start at
$9,000.
</P>
<P>
   Also from Korea, Kia recently entered the New England market
with a small sedan and sport utility vehicle. Both vehicles are in
the low price range.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   There's a lot that's new out there. Volkswagen has just about
totally revamped its lineup from the new Beetle and Golf to the
Jetta and Passat . . . Acura has a new mid-priced 3.2TL that's
loaded with features . . . Audi has a sporty A6 Avant wagon
available with all-wheel-drive . . . BMW is beginning the
introduction of a new 3-series. Only the sedan is currently
available.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Want more? Chrysler has revived a grand name in its standout
300M performance sedan . . . Infiniti has brought back the G20, a
nicely equipped introduction to the line . . . Mitsubishi has an
all new Galant that's longer, wider, taller and more of a performer
than in the past . . . Oldsmobile has a new Alero series is
well-equipped for under-$17,000 introductory price . . . The
Pontiac Grand Am is new and more powerful . . . Volvo is now all
front-drive with the introduction of its S80 sedan. The new
flagship replaces the old 900 series. Its packed with luxury,
safety and performance features . . . And even Rolls-Royce has a
new model, the Silver Seraph _ the company's first new car since
1980.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
