<HEADER>
A7033 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS &LR;      02-16 0418
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`SNAKES EYES'' A BAD ROLL; `SUNDAY' IS MARVELOUS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Snake Eyes'' _ Ever since Nicolas Cage won the
best-actor Oscar for ``Leaving Las Vegas,'' he's been on the
Stallone road to nowhere (unless, of course, you consider the bank
an appropriate destination). This outing with Brian De Palma at the
helm is another failed action movie with a great title and little
else.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sunday'' _ This low-key story about an old actress and a
homeless man whom she mistakes for a film director is marvelously
understated. Though flawed, the characters never look for pity, and
by the film's conclusion they've risen above our stereotypes and
achieved true artistry.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   INGRID BERGMAN: On Feb. 23, Fox Lorber introduces its World
Cinema Collection with six of Ingrid Bergman's Swedish films. In
Swedish with English subtitles, the features include ``Dollar''
(1938), ``A Woman's Face'' (1938), and ``June Night'' (1940).
</P>
<P>
   DVD UPDATE: DVD backers are waiting for Disney to put the full
force of its animated library behind the new digital technology.
While Disney previously released the direct-to-video title ``Beauty
and the Beast: Enchanted Christmas'' on DVD, its first big push
comes on April 20, when ``A Bug's Life'' will be released
simultaneously on DVD and VHS.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Feb. 23: ``Ronin,'' ``Carnival of Souls,''
``The Manchurian Candidate,'' ``Pecker.'' March 2: ``Dark City,''
``Tom and Jerry: The Movie,'' ``A Winter Tan,'' ``The Island of Dr.
Moreau.'' March 9: ``What Dreams May Come,'' ``Dead Man on
Campus,'' ``Black Dog,'' ``Slam,'' ``Somebody Is Waiting.'' March
16: ``The Waterboy,'' ``Bulworth,'' ``No Laughing Matter,''
``Living Out Loud,'' ``One True Thing,'' ``Polish Wedding,'' ``Paul
Monette: The Brink of Summer's End,'' ``Who the Hell Is
Juliette?,'' ``The Wonderful Ice Cream Suit.'' March 23:
``Pleasantville,'' ``Firelight,'' ``Bride of Chucky,'' ``Jerry
Springer's Ringmaster,'' ``From Dusk Till Dawn 2,'' ``Strike!''
March 30: ``The Rugrats Movie,'' ``Mutual Needs.'' April 6: ``A
Soldier's Daughter Never Cries,'' ``I Still Know What You Did Last
Summer,'' ``An Unexpected Life,'' ``Meet Joe Black,'' ``The Dentist
2.'' April 13: ``The Tempest,'' ``Bug Buster,'' ``Conspirators of
Pleasure.'' April 27: ``Happiness.'' May 4: ``Babe: Pig in the
City.'' May 11: ``Another Day in Paradise.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
