</P>
<P>
   The truth is that Clinton has always managed somehow to keep
separate the perceptions of his political and private lives.
</P>
<P>
   After all, ever since the Gennifer Flowers affair, the voters
have had no illusions about his moral standards (``He's slime,''
said one Washington doctor this week), but they have nonetheless
