of personal destruction.''
</P>
<P>
   And he has conducted ``the people's business'' with unmatched
political flair. Apart from the debacle of health-care reform in
1993, a failure of presidential inexperience and hubris, the
Clinton administrations have rarely stumbled.
</P>
<P>
   Instead, they have taken credit for achieving the Republican
goals of a balanced budget and a smaller government, while
