</P>
<P>
   DEAD-DOGS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ What killed the racing
greyhounds around the country? Latest tests indicate it was an
unusual form of a viral respiratory disease, not kennel cough.
Necropsies of three dead dogs, including Chances Are from West Palm
Beach, showed the dogs had severe internal bleeding. One of the
dead dogs had bacterial pneumonia associated with `e. coli' as a
complication of the suspected viral disease. Researchers are still
trying to isolate the exact virus. So what are kennel clubs doing?
(Donald, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   BAXTER-COLUMN _ The notion that public disgust with the
impeachment year might generate a big turnover in the next
congressional elections is being discounted both by Republican
strategists, who have reason to hope it won't be so, and Democrats,
who want to hedge their bets. All these predictions have the
classic earmarks of capital self-denial. Within the Beltway it is
hard to see this or admit it, but the most obvious impact of the
impeachment year is the profound toll it has taken on the prestige
of Washington itself. (Baxter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
MONDAY.
</P>
