written all over it. For two diners, a bottle each of red and white
is too much to drink. In most restaurants, the wines by the glass
are too humble to make a serious contribution to the meal. Unlike
the mind-body problem, the meat-fish problem has a solution. It's
the half bottle. By William Grimes.
