shipping facility, etc. This is paid for this time each year by the
co-op and the Florida Sugar Cane League, which represents the
Fanjuls and U.S. Sugar. Barring any damaging weather, Florida's raw
sugar crop will reach 2 million tons for the first time ever this
year. And because of rain delays, the harvest season, which usually
ends in March, will stretch into April. (Waresh, Palm Beach Post).
