 For Release WEDNESDAY AMs, February 17, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   OCALAN-PROTESTS (New York) _ Arrest of Kurdish rebel leader
Abdullah Ocalan triggers protests by Kurds in Greek embassies from
Moscow to London, causing scores of arrests and the hostage-taking
of Greek ambassadors. By Colum Lynch. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MA-DEATH-PENALTY (Boston) _ Governor re-files a bill calling for
the death penalty. Vote count in the legislature shifts due to
suddenly vacant seats and special elections. By Frank Phillips and
Scot Lehigh. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-REGISTRY (Boston) _ Automobile dealers charge $150 to $300 to
register cars even though it costs almost nothing to generate the
paperwork. By Bruce Mohl. 700 words. (a and f coding)
</P>
<P>
   JEHOVAS-TRANSFUSION (Boston) _ Appeals court says a judge erred
when he ruled that a 17-year-old member of the Jehovah's Witnesses
could be given a transfusion against her will. By John Ellement.
700 words.
</P>
<P>
   OBITUARY-KENDALL (Undated) _ MIT professor and Nobel prize
winner Henry Kendall dies in a diving accident. By David L.
Chandler. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   UNITED-GREENWALD (Boston) _ Air passengers may have cause for
rage, United Air Lines CEO Gerry Greenwald says, but the evidence
remains too weak to justify a Passenger Bill of rights. By Jerry
Ackereman. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   MACWORLD-NY (Undated) _ Macworld organizers say the show will
stay in New York City instead of returning to Boston as planned. By
Hiawatha Bray. 650 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SAILOR-RESCUE (Undated) _ Star French sailor is rescued in the
South Pacific by a rival in the solo around-the-world race. By Tony
Chamberlain. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Undated) _ Patriots running back Robert Edwards
has surgery on a knee injured during a flag football game on the
beach in Hawaii. By Will McDonough. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
