<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Wednesday, Feb. 17. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
IRAQFLAK (Undated) - It was supposed to be a routine refueling
flight well outside the no-fly zone over northern Iraq. But then
two streaking missles rose from the ground below. By DENNIS WAGNER.
Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
CLINTON (Phoenix) - President Bill Clinton will pay a visit to
Arizona on Feb. 25, the first time he has been here since the blitz
of three appearances he made here in September, October and
November of 1996 that resulted in his taking of the state in his
re-election campaign. The president will spend much of the day in
an event related to social security, according to Republic sources.
By CHRIS MOESER. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
SHEEHY-CLINTONS (Phoenix) - Journalist and author Gail Sheehy has
been tracking Bill and Hillary Clinton since the campaign of 1992.
In last month's ``Vanity Fair,'' she wrote an extensive article on
how the Clinton marriage is faring - now that the secret of Bill's
philandering is out. The verdict: Hillary is not amused. ``She's
putting him through the wringer,'' Sheehy says. By BARBARA YOST.
Story moved in the ``L'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BOOK-LOSTBIRD (Undated) _ In ``Looking for Lost Bird,'' Yvette
Melanson, raised white and Jewish after being stolen with her twin
brother from a hospital more than 40 years ago, tells of her
bittersweet return to her people on the Navajo Indian Reservation
in Arizona. By CAROL SOWERS. Story moved in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BOOKS-NEW (Undated) _ Capsule reviews of new and notable books. By
ANNE STEPHENSON. Story moved in the ``E'' category.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
NOTARO-COLUMN (Phoenix) - A couple of months ago, I wrote a nasty
letter to ``This Old House'' because I didn't like how a Victorian
mansion was being restored. After I mailed it, I realized that,
because I was being so petty, karma _ which returns to you ten-fold
_ was going to be brutal. I now believe that the following letters
are a portion of my penance. By LAURI NOTARO. Story moved in the
``L'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
