<P>
   ATM-CARJACK (Los Angeles) _ The LAPD mounted a manhunt Tuesday
for men who attacked a couple at an ATM around 10 p.m. Monday,
robbed and carjacked them and drove them around for several hours.
The man was beaten and the woman was sexually assaulted, then left
in an alley as the attackers made their getaway in another vehicle.
By Greg Gittrich. (Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   JET-CRASH (Los Angeles) _ A private jet overshot a Los
Angeles-area airport runway, skidded across a grassy area and
crashed into parked small planes and a fence Tuesday. The
Gulfstream II jet, with four people aboard, made a hard landing
about 1:15 p.m. at Van Nuys Airport and rolled past the end of the
runway. The crew of three and lone passenger weren't hurt. By
Yvette Cabrera and Greg Gittrich. (Will move in the ``n''
California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   OJ-HEISMAN (Los Angeles) _ Going, going gone! To the highest
bidder goes that Heisman Trophy belonging to O.J. Simpson,
auctioned by Butterfield &AMP; Butterfield in Los Angeles to pay the
football legend's judgment in the civil case won by the family of
his slain wife Nicole. By Jesse Heistand. (Will move in the ``n''
California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
