<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Azria getting his act together
 &HT;    By A. Scott Walton
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Max Azria designs like a man fighting for respect. If his next
cold weather collection for BCBG doesn't win it for him, nothing
will. Customers might notice that BCBG keeps rising in price, but
that's principally because Azria's designs are becoming
increasingly complex, luxurious, intelligent and desirable.
</P>
<P>
   Though bulky, his hand-knit sweaters and sweater dresses
accentuate the physique. Though militaristic in style, his suits
made the runway-weary models look dainty and sweet. Though
disparate, colors like cream and green and blue look unified thanks
to Azria's deft hand.
</P>
<P>
   A. Scott Walton writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
