<P>
   FOLD
</P>
<P>
   TX-DRAGGING-DEATH (Jasper, Texas) _ John William King, his arms
festooned with racist tattoos, had dreamed of forming his own local
chapter of a white supremacist group but felt he needed some
dramatic event to catapult him into the limelight and attract
members. That, prosecutors said for the first time, is their theory
of why King and two other young white men chained a 49-year-old
black man to the back of their pickup truck last June and dragged
him 3 miles down a country road until his flayed and battered body
fell apart. The case against King, 24, the first of the three
suspects to come to trial in the hideous death of James Byrd Jr.,
opens before a locally drawn jury of six men and five women _ all
white but for one black man. By Rick Lyman. (Scheduled to move by
8:30 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   NY-MRSCLINTON (New York) _ With New York Democrats in an uproar
over the potential Senate candidacy of Hillary Rodham Clinton, the
first lady's friends and advisers are warning her that a race could
be brutal, and that the easy victory predicted by state party
leaders is not at all guaranteed. By Elisabeth Bumiller. (Scheduled
to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   GLOBAL-ECON-III (Undated) _ Part three of the series on the
worldwide economic meltdown: From Asia to Russia to Brazil, markets
intertwined in sometimes dangerous ways. By Nicholas D. Kristoff
and Sheryl WuDunn. (The report has moved in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   With photos and graphics; 7,000 words.
</P>
<P>
   CT-POLICE-SHOOTING (New Milford, Conn.) _ Only a couple of
months ago, the future seemed so promising for Officer Scott Smith.
He had been filling in for a detective and showing the brass what
he could do. He had passed the all the tests of the Connecticut
State Police and hoped to become a trooper in training this summer.
But that was before he became the first police officer to be
charged with murder for shooting a criminal suspect. (Scheduled to
move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
