   &UR; GROWING &LR;  _ Question: I'm on the board of directors of a small
nonprofit. One of our employees, who is otherwise competent and
popular, has twice committed to large expenditures to help our
organization but without proper authorization. What would a
business do in this situation? Columnist Peter Sinton has the
answer.
