<SLUG> BC-LEVI-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 Levi's Sales Unraveled In 1998  &HT;       
 By Carol Emert 
 &HT;     c. 1999 San Francisco Chronicle 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
Dragged down by its flagship Levi's brand, sales at Levi Strauss &AMP;
Co. plunged 13 percent last year, the biggest sales decline at
least since World War II.
</P>
<P>
   Amid slumping demand worldwide, fiscal 1998 sales fell to $6
billion from $6.9 billion in 1997. Sales have dropped about 17
percent since peaking at $7.1 billion in 1996.
</P>
<P>
   Privately held Levi's does not report earnings, but spokesman
Gavin Power said the company was profitable despite sales declines
in all of its regions.
</P>
<P>
   Weakness at Levi's comes despite robust performance in the jeans
category. Total domestic sales of men's jeans grew 6.2 percent in
1998 while women's jeans rose 7.8 percent, according to NPD Group,
a research firm based in Port Washington, NY.
</P>
<P>
   On the men's side, Levi's market share has dropped from about 50
percent in the early 1990s to about half that level as consumers
have flocked to rival brands on both the high and low ends, said
Isaac Lagnado of Tactical Retail Solutions, a New York
apparel-industry consulting firm.
</P>
<P>
   Levi's problems are not confined to its flagship brand. Sales of
the company's Slates dress-pant line, which had been growing, were
flat last year despite healthy overall sales of tailored clothing.
</P>
<P>
   According to NPD Group, sales of men's tailored clothing rose
7.1 percent in 1998, making it one of the strongest segments of the
apparel industry.
</P>
<P>
   Power said executives consider Slates performance strong. ``That
category is not experiencing as much growth as khakis or some other
areas,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Lagnado said Slates competitors such as Haggar and Farah have
upgraded their fabrics and are doing a better job competing against
Slates.
</P>
<P>
   Levi's secondary line, Dockers, which consists mainly of khakis,
experienced record sales and profits last year.
</P>
<P>
   Broken down by region, Levi's sales in the Americas fell 18
percent to $3.9 billion, and they dropped 5.9 percent to $1.7
billion in Europe, the Middle East and Africa. Asia's economic
problems contributed to a 26.8 percent decline there, with total
sales of $369 million.
</P>
<P>
   The sales decline in fiscal 1998, which ended Nov. 29, 1998, is
the largest on record for the company since it began using modern
accounting methods in the 1940s, Power said. It is difficult to
compare earlier figures, he said.
</P>
<P>
   On the positive side, sales of Levi's teen-oriented fashion
lines, Silver Tab and L-2, exceeded expectations last year, Power
said.
</P>
<P>
   The company is planning to introduce another teen-oriented
sub-brand, which has not yet been named, with fashion products such
as cargo pants and carpenter pants.
</P>
<P>
   Launch of the new line was scheduled for this month and March
but now is slated for later this year.
</P>
<P>
   Levi's is planning several other initiatives to get the brand on
track. It continues to sponsor rock concerts and next month will
roll out a line of 1960s-inspired clothing tied to the release of a
movie based on the ``Mod Squad'' television show.
</P>
<P>
   Levi's also is planning to broaden its custom-made jeans
business, formerly called Personal Pair and recently renamed
Original Spin, in department stores and specialty stores across the
country during the next two to three years, Power said.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's nothing wrong with the strategy on paper,'' said
Lagnado. ``The question is, `How you do it.'''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
