rebuffed Tuesday in its attempt to acquire Mt. Vernon, N.Y.-based
Michael Anthony Jewelers Inc. in an all-cash transaction that would
have been worth more than $41 million. OroAmerica on Thursday had
sent to the Michael Anthony board of directors an unsolicited offer
to purchase all the company's 6.86 million common shares at their
$6 book value. Michael Anthony's board on Tuesday unanimously
rejected the offer, according to a statement issued after the stock
market closed. By Enrique Rivero. (Will move in the ``f'' financial
news file.)
