<HEADLINE>
NEW-LOOK MAVERICKS SEEM TO BE HEADED IN THE SAME OLD DIRECTION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DWAIN PRICE 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _.MDBU/ The .MDBU/Mavericks'.MDNM/ season is seven
games old, .MDBU/and.MDNM/ the.MDBU/y.MDNM/ are already stumbling
into a familiar hole. &QL; 
.MDNM/ Some touted this as a playoff team two weeks ago. So far,
though, this year's model looks surprising like the Mavericks who
have been in the NBA draft lottery each of the past eight seasons. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A young .MDBU/Mavericks .MDNM/team with four new players has
been hurt by a lockout-shortened training camp and a schedule that
has included Utah, Houston and Seattle, which .MDBU/were .MDNM/a
combined 15-1 heading into Tuesday's games. The Mavericks are 1-6
and tied with Denver for the second-worst record in the NBA. And
they trailed the Nuggets by 15 points at halftime of their loss in
Denver. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Coach/general manager Don Nelson has watched his team basically
play only one half of productive basketball every game, or have a
few players shine while others struggle. The total picture has been
devastating. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``We haven't had a game this year where we've hit on all of our
cylinders,'' Nelson said. ``There's always somebody who's not
playing well. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I can't wait until we start playing some games where
everybody's hitting and playing in the 90th percentile of their
game, because I still think we can be pretty good.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Mavericks have played five of their first seven on the road,
and the two home games were against Utah and Houston. But the
schedule doesn't get any easier with tonight's 9:30 game a.MDBU/t
the Los Angeles.MDNM/ Lakers and three more games left on a
seven-game, 11-day road trip. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a horrible schedule for us, and we've somehow got to
figure out how to become better in a really tough situation,''
center Shawn Bradley said. ``The lockout really, really hurt teams
like us that are trying to get better.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Bradley has not been able to unlock his game so far this season.
His scoring is down from 11.4 points per game last season to 5.6
and his rebounds have dropped from 8.1 to 5.9 per game. Starting
guard Michael Finley has also struggled; his scoring has dropped
from 21.5 points per game last season to 17.0 this season and he's
shooting 38.9 percent from the field.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Point guard Steve Nash hasn't found his shooting touch, hitting
33.8 percent of his attempts, though he is averaging 6.3 assists
per game. The up-and-down play of rookie Dirk Nowitzki has led
Nelson to running a revolving door at forward that has included
A.C. Green, Samaki Walker, Gary Trent and .MDBU/John .MDNM/``Hot
Rod'' Williams playing significant minutes at different times. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   As a team, the Mavericks are shooting .MDBU/only
.MDNM/40.MDBU/..MDNM/8 .MDBU/percent .MDNM/from the field and are
being outscored, 25-21, in the first quarter. The Mavericks are
scoring 90.3 points per game and allowing 97.3. They also are being
outrebounded, 47.7 to 43.3 per game. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Nash said the Mavericks need some practice time to work out
their problems. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel bad for coach .MDBU/\R.MDNM/Nelson.MDBU/\S.MDNM/
because he's out there calling plays and he doesn't have a lot of
time to correct the mistakes that we're making on the practice
floor,'' he said. ``He can draw them on the chalkboard, but we
don't get a chance to really run through them and try to practice
on the offense because of the short season. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``We had two weeks of practice before we saw what was going to
